## Issue description

The `gil_scoped_acquire` guard can in some cases require the GIL, because it calls detail::get_internals(), which calls into the Python CAPI if` get_internals` hasn't already been called with the GIL held in the current module.

Reproduced with Pybind 2.2.2, CPython 2.7.13; issue still appears in pybind11 master.

## Reproducible example code

Contrived example:

```
// noddy.cpp
#include <Python.h>
#include <pybind11/pybind11.h>

PyMODINIT_FUNC
initnoddy(void) 
{
    Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS  // release the GIL
    {
        pybind11::scoped_gil_release guard;  // <-- first pybind call in this module
        // Bang!
    }

    Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS  // release the GIL
}
```

